ERIC L. ANSEL

Eric L. Ansel, founded Ansel & Miller, LLC in 1984 and has been practicing personal injury law for 40 years. He is recognized as one of the most successful personal injury trial attorneys in the country and has won many prestigious awards.

Mr. Ansel was recognized by a revered publication that covers legal and business news. The Daily Business Review recently selected Eric Ansel as a finalist for the title of Most Effective Lawyer in the field of Personal Injury.

Having earned a reputation as a highly skilled and aggressive litigator, clients have continuously received significant verdicts and settlements, in Florida and New York. His arguments before the judicial system, have resulted in landmark decisions that broaden personal injury verdicts

The National Law Journal determined that Mr. Ansel had won the 52nd largest verdict in the entire country, when his firm won a judgment against Yamaha for $39 million. This also resulted in one of the highest personal injury verdicts in the country.

Mr. Ansel earned his law degree at the University of Miami and his bachelor's degree from the University of Florida. He is a member of the Florida Bar and the American Trial Lawyers Association, an invitation extended only to those attorneys who exemplify superior qualifications, leadership, reputation, influence, stature, and profile as trial lawyers.
RONALD L. MILLER

Ronald L. Miller specializes in all areas of personal injury and has been practicing law for 35 years.

Mr. Miller started his career working for the Treasury Department and left in the late 1970s to redirect his legal expertise into a field where he could help people.

He is a recognized lawyer with extensive experience and a proven track record in representing individuals and families in all areas of personal injury. His specialty is negotiating and obtaining maximum amounts in pre-trial settlements.

Mr. Miller earned his law degree from the University of Miami and acquired his bachelor's degree in accounting from Florida State University. He is also a member of the Florida Bar.
SAMUEL J. SIMON

Samuel J. Simon specializes in Personal Injury Litigation, including catastrophic automobile negligence claims, no fault claims, medical malpractice, product and premises liability.

For over 40 years Sam Simon has successfully negotiated and tried many multiple million dollar claims for victims of accidental injuries.

Mr. Simon earned his law degree from Boston University where he ranked top of his class after earning a Bachelors in Science from the State University of New York at Binghamton. He is also a member of the American Association for Justice, the Florida Justice Association, and the Florida Bar. He has also been admitted to the US District Court, Southern District.
MICHAEL PALAHACH III

Michael Palahach is of counsel to the firm and has practiced in Florida for over 40 years specializing in civil litigation and personal injury including extensive Federal Court litigation.  He is a true leader in his profession and one of the country’s most respected trial lawyers.

Mr.Palahach is a Board Certified Civil Trial Lawyer by the Florida Bar, and a Florida Supreme Court Certified Circuit Civil Mediator.

He attended the University of Florida where he earned his Bachelor of Science in Business Administration in 1970 and played for the Florida Gators Football team from 1966 to 1969. He received his Juris Doctor from the University of Florida College of Law in 1973. 
JOVANNI C. FIALLO

Jovanni C. Fiallo is an associate litigation attorney, specializing in admiralty/maritime law. He earned his law degree from Ave Maria School of Law, where he served as the President of the Student Bar Association, President of the Moot Court Board, and was also a Governor on the Florida Bar’s Young Lawyers Division Law School Division, sworn in by Justice Perry.

Mr. Fiallo received his B.A. at Saint Leo University where he majored in Criminal Justice and minored in Psychology – he was also the starting catcher on the Baseball team.

Mr. Fiallo is a member of the Florida Bar and the American Bar Association. He is also admitted to practice in the United States District Court for the Southern District of Florida.
 



